The paper describes a hardware implementation of the extreme learning machine (ELM) for machine learning applications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the design space tradeoff between speed, power, and accuracy, which could also place it in the sub-categories of Architecture (cs.AR) and Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). The paper also demonstrates both regression and classification on UCI data sets, which could place it in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Engineering and Control (cs.EM).
